WEBVTT

00:00.270 --> 00:01.940
Previously on "Devious maids"...

00:01.950 --> 00:03.630
So you saw a dvd in the safe?

00:03.665 --> 00:05.275
It had Flora's name on it.

00:05.310 --> 00:07.670
That has to be the one.
You've got to get it.

00:07.705 --> 00:10.030
I will marry you if I
can still be a father.

00:10.065 --> 00:11.765
Exactly what are you suggesting?

00:11.800 --> 00:15.020
I want Valentina to
give us one of her eggs.

00:15.055 --> 00:16.219
Where's his suitcase?

00:16.254 --> 00:17.065
What's going on?

00:17.100 --> 00:19.185
- You're going back to rehab.
- What?!

00:19.220 --> 00:21.080
I didn't know you and
Mr. Powell had a son.

00:21.115 --> 00:23.835
We don't anymore. He was killed.

00:23.870 --> 00:25.840
It's been a long time since
I've enjoyed the company

00:25.875 --> 00:27.405
of such an adorable child.

00:27.440 --> 00:29.870
Brought back a lot
of wonderful memories.

00:30.050 --> 00:32.770
I saw the cytoxan in
your medicine cabinet.

00:32.900 --> 00:34.440
That's what the
doctors gave my mother.

00:34.475 --> 00:35.730
She had cancer?

00:35.940 --> 00:37.690
- Have you told Alejandro?
- No.

00:38.040 --> 00:39.390
Nobody knows.

00:43.900 --> 00:45.605
All the suits have
listened to the new CD.

00:45.640 --> 00:47.720
You know what word they're
starting to toss around?

00:47.950 --> 00:49.050
"Genius."

00:49.860 --> 00:51.115
Well, that's nice,

00:51.150 --> 00:52.980
but I don't think it's ready yet.

00:53.420 --> 00:54.900
The gazpacho is ready.

00:55.100 --> 00:56.410
Uh, we'll be right there.

00:58.750 --> 00:59.750
Odessa,

01:00.140 --> 01:02.070
who's that guy having
lunch with Alejandro?

01:02.105 --> 01:04.349
His agent, Jackson Narino.

01:04.440 --> 01:06.790
He's slimy, but very important.

01:06.910 --> 01:08.350
Did you finish the salad?

01:08.430 --> 01:10.280
Two hours ago. It's in the fridge.

01:10.315 --> 01:11.300
Good.

01:13.180 --> 01:14.390
You look awful.

01:14.720 --> 01:16.360
And you dress like a tramp.

01:16.730 --> 01:18.820
Isn't it nice we can be
honest with each other?

01:18.830 --> 01:21.850
Seriously, I'm worried about you.

01:21.950 --> 01:23.610
Has the chemo been terrible?

01:23.720 --> 01:25.490
Well, it's not for sissies.

01:26.120 --> 01:27.740
When are you gonna tell
Alejandro you're sick?

01:27.775 --> 01:29.370
- I can't.
- Why not?

01:29.380 --> 01:31.070
He would be devastated.

01:31.660 --> 01:33.890
Besides, he has so much
on his mind right now.

01:34.080 --> 01:34.515
Odessa.

01:34.550 --> 01:35.860
I am not telling him!

01:35.870 --> 01:37.520
And I'm sorry I told you.

01:41.020 --> 01:42.285
I didn't mean that.

01:42.320 --> 01:43.550
I'm just tired.

01:45.650 --> 01:46.730
It's fine.

01:49.240 --> 01:50.335
Oh, my god.

01:50.370 --> 01:51.230
- Odessa.
- Yes?

01:51.265 --> 01:52.270
Your hair!

01:52.480 --> 01:53.275
What about it?

01:53.310 --> 01:55.100
- It's falling out.
- What?!

01:55.135 --> 01:56.240
Oh, my god!

01:56.340 --> 01:57.640
It must be the chemo.

01:57.890 --> 01:59.185
Oh, my god!

01:59.220 --> 02:00.680
Odessa, it's everywhere.

02:00.715 --> 02:02.140
Look, it's on the cake...

02:02.175 --> 02:03.152
And the sandwiches!

02:03.187 --> 02:04.130
How did I not see this?

02:04.165 --> 02:05.400
I don't know!

02:07.150 --> 02:08.235
- The soup!
- The soup!

02:08.270 --> 02:09.639
The whole time I
was listening to it,

02:09.675 --> 02:11.005
I was thinking... "Grammy."

02:11.039 --> 02:12.810
- I think you're being very polite.
- No.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.190
- What the...
- It's time for the salad.

02:17.225 --> 02:18.820
But we haven't tasted the soup yet.

02:18.855 --> 02:20.250
You had your chance.

02:22.650 --> 02:24.080
She's Russian.

02:26.000 --> 02:32.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:45.680 --> 02:46.620
Come in!

02:49.940 --> 02:51.140
Did you talk to him?

02:51.280 --> 02:52.340
Yes.

02:54.890 --> 02:56.530
He's agreed to a settlement.

02:57.230 --> 02:57.705
Really?

02:57.740 --> 03:01.030
Only in exchange for a graceful end

03:01.230 --> 03:02.540
to the situation.

03:02.950 --> 03:03.885
What does that mean?

03:03.920 --> 03:05.650
It means if you
keep your mouth shut,

03:06.290 --> 03:07.590
you get this check.

03:11.510 --> 03:12.800
Are you kidding me?

03:12.850 --> 03:14.065
That's very generous.

03:14.100 --> 03:16.430
This is nothing.
Your client raped me.

03:16.465 --> 03:18.030
But how is that possible?

03:18.650 --> 03:19.405
You're a prostitute.

03:19.440 --> 03:21.460
You were paid to have sex with him.

03:21.560 --> 03:23.425
As soon as I found out who he was,

03:23.460 --> 03:25.290
I told him to stop. He didn't.

03:25.325 --> 03:26.515
That's called rape.

03:26.550 --> 03:28.070
And that gets me a
hell of a lot more

03:28.105 --> 03:29.860
than this lousy check.

03:31.980 --> 03:33.405
I'm not sure what
happened that night.

03:33.440 --> 03:34.795
All I know is you don't have proof.

03:34.830 --> 03:36.820
Without that, we don't
back up the money truck

03:36.855 --> 03:38.120
to your doorstep.

03:38.970 --> 03:41.910
Okay. What do I get for a baby?

03:43.540 --> 03:44.500
What?

03:45.530 --> 03:46.660
That's right.

03:46.870 --> 03:48.260
I'm pregnant.

03:49.240 --> 03:52.520
Are you saying that my
client is the father?

03:52.640 --> 03:55.810
No, but he knows who is.

03:56.130 --> 03:58.260
And they are very close.

03:59.750 --> 04:00.835
Oh, god.

04:00.870 --> 04:04.250
Now I have bills to pay,
and a grandmother to support.

04:04.285 --> 04:06.357
So I need a check immediately.

04:06.392 --> 04:08.285
And when I deposit this thing,

04:08.320 --> 04:11.370
I want to see the bank teller gasp.

04:12.730 --> 04:13.810
You got it?

04:14.920 --> 04:17.010
You have no idea who
you're screwing with.

04:17.890 --> 04:20.779
I've seen this guy in
action. He is beyond vicious.

04:21.410 --> 04:23.530
And if you back him into a corner,

04:25.220 --> 04:27.170
there's no telling
what he might do.

04:32.310 --> 04:33.710
I'm not worried.

04:42.230 --> 04:44.355
This is the DVD Rosie found?

04:44.390 --> 04:46.480
Adrian kept it in his safe.

04:46.530 --> 04:49.650
I don't see why. It's
a whole lot of nothing.

04:50.410 --> 04:52.065
Well, I don't think so.

04:52.100 --> 04:55.300
It proves that Michael
Stappord knows who raped Flora.

04:55.335 --> 04:56.970
He was representing the guy.

04:57.005 --> 04:58.585
At $600 an hour,

04:58.620 --> 05:00.920
you can bet he's taking
that name to the grave.

05:00.955 --> 05:02.005
Can't the judge make him tell?

05:02.040 --> 05:04.915
He basically admitted that
his client was violent.

05:04.950 --> 05:08.750
He'll say he was exaggerating
to get Flora to lower her price.

05:09.810 --> 05:10.970
God.

05:14.100 --> 05:15.550
I hate lawyers.

05:15.810 --> 05:17.760
We did learn one useful thing.

05:19.210 --> 05:22.350
The man that raped her is
not the father of her baby.

05:22.450 --> 05:25.390
And there is some kind of
connection between them.

05:25.640 --> 05:27.330
So which one killed her?

05:27.520 --> 05:28.335
My theory was always,

05:28.370 --> 05:30.130
a guy who rapes is
more likely to kill.

05:30.165 --> 05:31.260
I don't know.

05:31.440 --> 05:32.570
There are an awful
lot of guys out there

05:32.580 --> 05:34.490
who don't want to
pay child support.

05:34.860 --> 05:37.220
So... now we just

05:37.230 --> 05:39.780
need to find out
who the father was.

05:39.800 --> 05:42.750
Is there anyone
Flora might have told?

05:42.820 --> 05:44.580
Someone we overlooked?

05:44.615 --> 05:45.950
On the DVD...

05:46.310 --> 05:48.960
didn't she say something
about a grandmother?

05:52.710 --> 05:54.760
It's his birthday!

05:56.000 --> 05:57.890
He turns 1 year old today.

05:57.900 --> 06:00.120
When Mrs. Peri gets back
from New York on Friday,

06:00.155 --> 06:02.670
we're gonna have cake and presents.

06:03.640 --> 06:04.800
Can I come?

06:05.420 --> 06:07.840
Well, it--it's just
me and the family.

06:08.040 --> 06:10.170
Would it be weird for me
to drop in unannounced?

06:10.205 --> 06:12.217
I can tell them
I'm Tucker's friend.

06:12.252 --> 06:14.230
And bring a ridiculously
expensive gift.

06:14.680 --> 06:16.670
Yes, that would be weird.

06:16.890 --> 06:17.870
Which part?

06:18.750 --> 06:19.920
All of it.

06:20.570 --> 06:22.090
Well, it was just a thought.

06:23.030 --> 06:24.595
I'm gonna give him
some strained peaches.

06:24.630 --> 06:26.160
That'll give you time
to finish this floor.

06:26.470 --> 06:27.340
Okay.

06:30.750 --> 06:32.440
But it won't take too long.

06:37.840 --> 06:38.680
Hello there.

06:40.960 --> 06:42.420
Oh, you're back.

06:43.240 --> 06:45.630
Hi. I'm Rosie, your new maid.

06:46.100 --> 06:47.380
Are you really?

06:48.140 --> 06:48.885
Tell me, Rosie,

06:48.920 --> 06:51.550
uh, where is that bunion
that I'm married to?

06:51.750 --> 06:52.815
Mrs. Evelyn?

06:52.850 --> 06:55.410
She's in the kitchen with the baby.

06:56.120 --> 06:57.840
Baby? What baby?

06:58.790 --> 07:00.770
I also work for Peri Westmore.

07:00.950 --> 07:02.870
I bring her son here while I clean.

07:03.260 --> 07:04.500
You've done this before?

07:04.640 --> 07:05.910
Many times.

07:08.820 --> 07:09.920
Since you've been
bringing him here,

07:09.955 --> 07:11.230
has, uh, Evelyn...

07:12.380 --> 07:14.550
grown attached to the boy?

07:15.420 --> 07:16.830
How do you know that?

07:17.260 --> 07:18.900
Listen to me, do us both a favor.

07:18.980 --> 07:21.680
Take that child out of this house

07:22.420 --> 07:24.260
and never bring him back here.

07:25.050 --> 07:26.170
Do you understand?

07:27.300 --> 07:30.740
Not really. But I'll go get him.

07:31.660 --> 07:32.580
And, Rosie?

07:33.750 --> 07:37.190
Obviously, you can come
back anytime you want.

07:47.390 --> 07:48.890
Who's all this for?

07:49.010 --> 07:49.950
You.

07:50.540 --> 07:51.390
Me?

07:51.540 --> 07:52.610
Yes.

07:52.900 --> 07:54.980
I made sandwiches!

07:55.500 --> 07:57.510
You don't know how
to make sandwiches.

07:57.545 --> 07:59.500
Well, I know how to order them.

07:59.640 --> 08:01.550
It's practically the same thing.

08:01.980 --> 08:03.600
Please, sit.

08:03.630 --> 08:05.500
Tell me what you want first.

08:05.560 --> 08:06.570
Zoila.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.920
You only get domestic
when you want something.

08:08.955 --> 08:10.585
So let's just skip the roast beef

08:10.620 --> 08:12.410
and go straight to
the ulterior motive.

08:12.445 --> 08:13.625
All I'm trying to do

08:13.660 --> 08:17.040
is have a little
celebration with my friend.

08:17.470 --> 08:20.710
Alfred has agreed to marry me.

08:20.745 --> 08:23.950
Oh, honey! I'm so happy for you.

08:24.770 --> 08:26.260
Thank you.

08:29.130 --> 08:32.445
Now... try the ones with the pesto.

08:32.480 --> 08:35.760
I know how much you love pesto.

08:36.760 --> 08:39.120
So Alfred gave up on
the whole baby thing?

08:39.130 --> 08:41.679
No. He still wants to be a father.

08:41.870 --> 08:45.870
We'll just find a surrogate
to carry the child.

08:45.905 --> 08:47.315
Alfred's lawyer knows

08:47.350 --> 08:49.610
an Ivy League coed who might do it.

08:50.010 --> 08:51.875
That's fantastic.

08:51.910 --> 08:54.180
Of course, we'll also need an egg.

08:54.550 --> 08:56.280
And that's the tricky part.

08:56.740 --> 08:59.710
Alfred doesn't want
some anonymous donor.

09:00.100 --> 09:03.590
He wants the egg to come
from someone we... know and...

09:04.310 --> 09:05.520
trust.

09:11.340 --> 09:13.780
Please tell me you're not
gonna ask me for one of my eggs.

09:15.900 --> 09:17.460
Heavens, no.

09:17.730 --> 09:20.560
Your eggs are almost
as ossified as mine.

09:22.050 --> 09:23.020
Good.

09:23.600 --> 09:25.800
Because I was about
to spit out this pesto

09:25.835 --> 09:27.250
and throw it at you.

09:29.020 --> 09:29.865
No...

09:29.900 --> 09:32.030
we don't want one of your eggs.

09:32.850 --> 09:36.220
We want one of... Valentina's.

09:39.490 --> 09:43.470
Obviously, I wanted to
discuss this with you first.

09:43.700 --> 09:45.310
Aren't you considerate?

09:46.780 --> 09:48.140
Don't be angry.

09:48.340 --> 09:50.145
It's really a compliment.

09:50.180 --> 09:53.930
Alfred thinks Valentina
is bright and lovely--

09:53.965 --> 09:55.430
I don't care.

09:56.240 --> 09:58.150
That old man is not
gonna get his hands

09:58.185 --> 10:00.560
on my daughter's D.N.A.

10:03.240 --> 10:04.865
I know it's a lot to ask.

10:04.900 --> 10:07.710
I don't think you have any
idea what you've asked for,

10:07.745 --> 10:11.460
or how incredibly
insulting this is.

10:11.660 --> 10:12.610
Zoila!

10:13.870 --> 10:16.650
If Valentina doesn't do this,

10:16.685 --> 10:18.640
Alfred will leave me.

10:18.790 --> 10:20.940
Well, then get ready
to say, "Sayonara,"

10:20.975 --> 10:23.235
because it's not gonna happen.

10:23.270 --> 10:25.860
And you are forbidden
from saying a word of this

10:25.895 --> 10:27.940
to Valentina. Do you understand me?

10:34.380 --> 10:36.380
Alejandro, do you have a minute?

10:36.980 --> 10:38.740
Well, I'm sort of working here.

10:38.860 --> 10:39.870
I'm sorry.

10:39.900 --> 10:40.750
It's just...

10:40.760 --> 10:42.420
Odessa has something to tell you.

10:45.270 --> 10:47.670
Obviously, I've been tired lately.

10:47.930 --> 10:49.750
I'm sure you've noticed.

10:50.500 --> 10:52.570
Uh... not really.

10:56.630 --> 10:58.020
The truth is...

10:58.770 --> 10:59.990
I am sick.

11:01.000 --> 11:02.115
I did not want to tell you

11:02.150 --> 11:04.120
because I did not
want you to worry.

11:05.230 --> 11:06.510
Well, that's nice of you.

11:09.610 --> 11:12.550
But I am getting worse.

11:12.560 --> 11:15.050
So we can no longer
keep this a secret.

11:17.150 --> 11:18.570
I have cancer.

11:22.870 --> 11:24.100
Is it serious?

11:25.750 --> 11:27.120
It's cancer.

11:27.960 --> 11:29.900
Yeah, right. Sorry.

11:31.800 --> 11:33.775
So do you need some time off?

11:33.810 --> 11:35.750
No. It's good for me to work.

11:35.785 --> 11:38.315
But while I'm in chemo,

11:38.350 --> 11:40.360
I may have to cut back on hours.

11:40.370 --> 11:42.600
But you don't have to worry
about getting things done.

11:42.635 --> 11:43.645
I can do both jobs.

11:43.680 --> 11:45.570
I am so grateful to Carmen.

11:45.590 --> 11:48.690
She has been... a godsend.

11:48.750 --> 11:49.910
I'm happy to help.

11:55.430 --> 11:56.960
I'm sorry. Is there anything else?

11:58.360 --> 11:59.180
No.

12:01.690 --> 12:03.080
Thank you for your time.

12:11.070 --> 12:11.885
What would you say

12:11.920 --> 12:14.240
if someone told you
they had a fatal disease?

12:14.275 --> 12:15.235
If it was contagious,

12:15.270 --> 12:16.620
I'd tell them to sit over there.

12:17.310 --> 12:19.200
Someone I know has cancer.

12:19.270 --> 12:22.050
Great, now I feel
like a jerk. Thank you.

12:22.140 --> 12:23.830
Who's got cancer?

12:23.990 --> 12:25.120
It's a secret.

12:25.300 --> 12:27.270
I swore on my life I wouldn't tell.

12:27.690 --> 12:29.220
I'll let you have a churro.

12:29.310 --> 12:30.550
It's Odessa.

12:31.900 --> 12:34.150
- Odessa has cancer?
- Yes.

12:34.180 --> 12:35.760
And she told
Alejandro she was sick,

12:35.795 --> 12:37.710
and he barely reacted.

12:37.850 --> 12:39.495
Well, that doesn't
mean he doesn't care.

12:39.530 --> 12:42.770
Some people work hard at
suppressing their emotions.

12:42.805 --> 12:44.737
I once dropped this guy's Grammy,

12:44.772 --> 12:46.670
and he cried like a little girl.

12:46.680 --> 12:48.120
Maybe he was in shock.

12:48.155 --> 12:48.800
No.

12:48.810 --> 12:51.000
I looked into his eyes.
There was no concern,

12:51.035 --> 12:53.490
no compassion. I don't get it.

12:53.540 --> 12:55.825
She has been with
him for ten years.

12:55.860 --> 12:58.110
He's probably more
upset than you think.

12:58.145 --> 12:59.470
You should talk to him.

12:59.990 --> 13:01.450
It would be nice to be wrong.

13:02.510 --> 13:04.810
I gotta go. I'll
see you girls later.

13:04.845 --> 13:05.550
Okay.

13:09.310 --> 13:11.130
This whole thing make you think.

13:11.790 --> 13:12.630
About?

13:12.670 --> 13:14.150
The people we work for.

13:14.840 --> 13:16.860
If we died, would they really care?

13:17.280 --> 13:18.725
Sure, they would.

13:18.760 --> 13:21.590
They might come to our
funeral, shed a tear or two.

13:22.230 --> 13:25.140
But after a few weeks, would
they still think about us

13:25.175 --> 13:27.080
and all we've done for their lives?

13:27.680 --> 13:29.040
It would depend.

13:29.250 --> 13:30.390
On what?

13:31.140 --> 13:33.720
How good the maid
was that replaced us.

13:39.420 --> 13:42.340
Good morning, Mr.
Pettigrove. How are you doing?

13:42.500 --> 13:45.510
I'm in dreadful need of some tea.

13:45.545 --> 13:46.960
I'll get the kettle on.

13:48.420 --> 13:51.395
You know, I've been
here for a few days now,

13:51.430 --> 13:54.370
and it occurs to me I
know so little about you.

13:54.405 --> 13:55.970
There's not much to know.

13:56.280 --> 13:59.090
Why don't you tell me
about your ambitions?

13:59.125 --> 14:00.395
I'm sure you have dreams

14:00.430 --> 14:02.750
that extend beyond domestic work.

14:02.940 --> 14:06.490
Oh, I do. I want to be a designer.

14:06.700 --> 14:09.500
I'll bet you're very talented.

14:09.750 --> 14:10.950
I hope so.

14:11.790 --> 14:14.170
You planning on opening
your own boutique?

14:14.205 --> 14:15.115
First I want to go to

14:15.150 --> 14:17.820
the Los Angeles Academy
of Fashion and Design.

14:18.270 --> 14:20.140
I was accepted there last year.

14:20.540 --> 14:22.360
Then why aren't you in school?

14:22.760 --> 14:24.480
My family can't afford the tuition,

14:24.490 --> 14:27.010
and we are not poor
enough for financial aid.

14:28.560 --> 14:30.850
That's a cruel irony.

14:31.220 --> 14:33.710
That's why I'm working
here-- save money.

14:34.640 --> 14:37.920
How long till you have
the necessary funds?

14:37.955 --> 14:39.150
Couple of years.

14:40.270 --> 14:42.220
It's a really expensive school.

14:44.250 --> 14:45.780
What if I told you there was

14:45.790 --> 14:49.380
a quick and easy way
to get that money?

14:51.750 --> 14:52.980
What do you mean?

14:53.360 --> 14:55.990
Oh, I'm not suggesting
anything untoward.

14:56.025 --> 14:57.000
It's just...

14:57.650 --> 14:59.430
you have something I need.

15:04.700 --> 15:05.825
Excuse me.

15:05.860 --> 15:07.930
- Are you Mirta Hernandez?
- No.

15:07.965 --> 15:09.870
Mirta's my roommate.

15:10.360 --> 15:12.800
I'm Birdie. Birdie Gladwell.

15:12.880 --> 15:14.420
Do you know where she is?

15:14.470 --> 15:15.590
I need to talk to her.

15:15.625 --> 15:16.835
In the courtyard.

15:16.870 --> 15:19.380
Her grandson came for a visit.

15:20.090 --> 15:22.180
No one ever visits me.

15:22.215 --> 15:24.270
Everyone I know is dead.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.790
Yes. Well...

15:28.430 --> 15:30.770
Thank you for your
help, Mrs. Gladwell.

15:30.805 --> 15:32.120
It's "Miss."

15:32.670 --> 15:34.420
I was a lesbian.

15:36.510 --> 15:37.930
Courtyard, you say?

15:51.100 --> 15:52.210
Hey there.

15:53.020 --> 15:54.690
Are you Mirta?

15:54.750 --> 15:55.830
Can I help you?

15:56.110 --> 15:56.985
I hope so.

15:57.020 --> 15:58.250
Is this your grandmother?

15:58.285 --> 15:59.080
Yeah.

15:59.510 --> 16:01.960
Then you must be related
to Flora Hernandez.

16:01.995 --> 16:04.440
Yeah, uh, she was my cousin.

16:05.560 --> 16:06.480
Who are you?

16:06.500 --> 16:08.870
Oh, my name is Marisol.

16:09.050 --> 16:11.420
I need to ask your
grandmother a few questions.

16:11.455 --> 16:14.060
About Flora? No way.

16:14.310 --> 16:16.230
Please. It's important.

16:16.460 --> 16:18.840
My grandmother doesn't
talk about her anymore.

16:19.070 --> 16:20.530
She gets upset.

16:20.850 --> 16:23.035
Listen, I have reason to believe

16:23.070 --> 16:25.380
that the police
arrested the wrong man

16:25.415 --> 16:26.740
for your cousin's murder.

16:26.920 --> 16:29.950
- What?
- And she may have said something to your grandmother

16:29.985 --> 16:32.250
that could help us find
out who really killed her.

16:32.820 --> 16:34.990
My grandma can't help anyone.

16:35.010 --> 16:36.210
The truth is...

16:36.470 --> 16:38.670
she's just not all there anymore.

16:43.840 --> 16:44.850
Are you sure?

16:46.020 --> 16:48.380
Because she seems
pretty interested to me.

16:51.990 --> 16:53.750
You have to leave now.

16:54.340 --> 16:57.325
Don't you think that
Flora deserves justice?

16:57.360 --> 17:00.310
Flora was an embarrassment
to our family.

17:00.770 --> 17:03.830
She was a liar, a
thief, and a whore.

17:04.040 --> 17:05.425
And as far as I'm concerned,

17:05.460 --> 17:07.369
she already got what she deserved.

17:08.400 --> 17:10.285
Tell reception that my grandmother

17:10.319 --> 17:12.170
is no longer accepting visitors.

17:13.390 --> 17:14.560
You got that?

17:20.380 --> 17:22.680
So how come you're not
going back to the Powells'?

17:23.319 --> 17:26.579
I think maybe Mrs. Evelyn
is a little strange.

17:26.680 --> 17:29.730
Well, I'm glad you were able
to earn some extra money.

17:29.765 --> 17:30.920
That was nice.

17:30.930 --> 17:31.825
But now that you're back,

17:31.860 --> 17:33.830
I'd rather be here
looking after you.

17:34.460 --> 17:36.170
So, is Tucker asleep?

17:36.470 --> 17:38.070
Yeah, I just put him down.

17:38.150 --> 17:38.925
Excellent.

17:38.960 --> 17:40.330
What are you doing?

17:40.490 --> 17:42.200
My doctor said I
needed to exercise.

17:42.235 --> 17:44.250
Hmm, in that case...

17:45.630 --> 17:46.620
What's this?

17:46.840 --> 17:48.860
Stuff you can help me with.

17:49.950 --> 17:51.620
Fix the doorbell, hang the mirror,

17:51.630 --> 17:52.735
hook up the new tv.

17:52.770 --> 17:54.410
Now this is not
the kind of exercise

17:54.445 --> 17:54.955
that I had in mind.

17:54.990 --> 17:57.270
I know what you had in
mind, and the answer is "No."

17:57.280 --> 17:58.345
Oh, come on.

17:58.380 --> 18:00.620
I missed you so much.
Didn't you miss me?

18:00.770 --> 18:04.360
No! You can't be doing that.

18:04.950 --> 18:06.910
- Why not?
- I told you.

18:06.945 --> 18:08.870
You just had a heart attack.

18:08.905 --> 18:10.070
Please.

18:11.160 --> 18:13.930
My heart stops
every time I see you.

18:15.980 --> 18:20.910
Okay. We can have sex,
but just to be safe...

18:21.250 --> 18:22.880
Let me do all the work.

