18:59.440 --> 19:00.620
Hello, Mrs. Evelyn.

19:00.650 --> 19:01.580
Rosie.

19:02.360 --> 19:04.180
I had a feeling you'd drop by.

19:10.230 --> 19:11.260
So...

19:12.640 --> 19:14.910
An affair with
Spence Westmore--

19:15.480 --> 19:17.340
That's a feather in your sombrero.

19:17.375 --> 19:18.915
I'm not proud of myself.

19:18.950 --> 19:21.640
I'm sure that will be
oh-so-soothing to Mrs. Westmore.

19:21.675 --> 19:23.990
See, that's why I'm here.

19:24.380 --> 19:27.075
Mrs. Peri can never
find out about this.

19:27.110 --> 19:29.530
- You think she'd be devastated?
- She would.

19:29.670 --> 19:32.110
And Mr. Spence doesn't
wanna get a divorce.

19:32.380 --> 19:34.550
He might lose custody of his son.

19:34.810 --> 19:36.255
Exactly.

19:36.290 --> 19:38.450
See, that's the
problem with adultery--

19:38.900 --> 19:41.010
the piper must be paid.

19:42.400 --> 19:44.705
I don't know who this piper is,

19:44.740 --> 19:47.010
but you can't tell him neither.

19:47.600 --> 19:50.160
I wouldn't dream of saying
a word to Peri Westmore.

19:50.170 --> 19:51.190
Do you know why?

19:52.700 --> 19:54.660
Because I consider you a friend.

19:54.690 --> 19:56.525
Oh, thank you.

19:56.560 --> 20:00.350
Which is why I was so hurt
when you stopped working here.

20:00.880 --> 20:02.630
A terse note left on
the kitchen counter--

20:02.665 --> 20:03.640
I deserve better than that.

20:03.675 --> 20:04.505
I'm sorry.

20:04.540 --> 20:07.450
It's just with Mr. Spence
being home from the hospital--

20:07.485 --> 20:10.420
I know. You had to
tend to his... needs.

20:11.430 --> 20:13.710
- I didn't mean to hurt you.
- But you did.

20:13.730 --> 20:14.465
You left me,

20:14.500 --> 20:16.330
and you took that sweet
little boy with you.

20:18.070 --> 20:19.510
I know it seems odd,

20:20.630 --> 20:23.440
but I've come to
depend upon that child.

20:23.475 --> 20:25.670
He brings color into my drab life,

20:25.705 --> 20:27.180
and I want him back.

20:28.430 --> 20:29.740
That can't happen.

20:29.775 --> 20:30.710
Why not?

20:31.320 --> 20:34.080
Well... it's complicated.

20:34.350 --> 20:36.690
No... it's not.

20:37.050 --> 20:38.535
You'll come twice a week.

20:38.570 --> 20:40.980
You will bring Tucker
Westmore, and in exchange,

20:41.015 --> 20:43.390
I will not tell the entire
city of Beverly Hills

20:43.425 --> 20:45.100
that his father's
screwing the maid.

20:46.250 --> 20:47.130
Now...

20:47.480 --> 20:49.760
what could be simpler than that?

21:00.140 --> 21:02.700
So... I have good news.

21:03.190 --> 21:05.610
Well, don't just keep
it to yourself. A ver.

21:05.980 --> 21:08.220
I'm gonna start fashion
school next fall.

21:09.540 --> 21:11.910
They changed their mind
about the scholarship!

21:12.900 --> 21:14.010
Not exactly.

21:15.130 --> 21:17.160
I found a way to pay the tuition.

21:18.210 --> 21:19.520
How did you do that?

21:20.560 --> 21:22.535
Mr. Pettigrove came to me.

21:22.570 --> 21:25.720
He told me about Mrs. Delatour
and what she asked you.

21:25.755 --> 21:26.685
Oh, my God.

21:26.720 --> 21:30.630
And now he's offering to pay
my tuition if I help them.

21:31.560 --> 21:33.150
Absolutely not.

21:33.780 --> 21:37.130
Mami... this is what
we always dreamed of.

21:37.165 --> 21:38.590
I'll get to go to school.

21:38.920 --> 21:41.100
By selling a part of yourself?

21:41.650 --> 21:44.160
I didn't raise you
to be this stupid

21:44.195 --> 21:45.740
or this desperate.

21:46.810 --> 21:48.680
I wouldn't just do this for myself.

21:48.890 --> 21:50.650
I'd be doing it for you, too.

21:51.100 --> 21:52.500
For me?

21:52.750 --> 21:55.030
I see the sacrifices you make,

21:55.070 --> 21:58.475
how hard you work on
weekends and holidays--

21:58.510 --> 22:01.100
just to make a few extra bucks
that you end up giving to me.

22:01.135 --> 22:02.700
I don't complain about that.

22:02.930 --> 22:04.640
Which makes it even worse!

22:06.480 --> 22:08.930
Now it's my chance to help you.

22:09.560 --> 22:10.865
If the tuition is paid for,

22:10.900 --> 22:13.160
you could finally stop
and take some time off.

22:13.195 --> 22:14.455
Do you really think

22:14.490 --> 22:17.540
that I would trade a
grandchild for a vacation?!

22:17.610 --> 22:18.900
It's just an egg.

22:19.590 --> 22:22.300
And this money would
change our lives.

22:22.335 --> 22:25.187
This decision would
change our lives

22:25.222 --> 22:28.040
in ways you can't
begin to understand.

22:31.110 --> 22:32.940
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

22:33.500 --> 22:35.640
But I will not
allow you to do this.

22:43.430 --> 22:45.000
Mami, you can't stop me.

22:47.290 --> 22:48.810
What did you say?

22:49.370 --> 22:51.555
It's my body, so it's my decision.

22:51.590 --> 22:53.740
And I'm doing this for both of us,

22:53.775 --> 22:55.570
whether you like it or not.

23:03.370 --> 23:04.345
You gotta be kidding!

23:04.380 --> 23:05.855
- I wish I was.
- I mean, come on!

23:05.890 --> 23:08.200
Who blackmails people to
have a chance to babysit?

23:08.235 --> 23:09.325
I know. It's weird.

23:09.360 --> 23:11.730
But Mrs. Evelyn is
obsessed with Tucker!

23:11.765 --> 23:14.100
- But why?
- I talked to my friend Marisol.

23:14.135 --> 23:16.060
She used to work for the Powells.

23:16.560 --> 23:18.800
She said they had a son who died.

23:21.550 --> 23:24.100
So she's working out her
emotional issues with my kid?

23:24.135 --> 23:25.360
Fantastic.

23:25.850 --> 23:26.915
What are we gonna do?

23:26.950 --> 23:29.530
Well, I'm not letting Tucker
within 50 feet of that lunatic.

23:29.565 --> 23:30.710
Obviously.

23:31.000 --> 23:33.790
But she will tell Mrs.
Peri about us, I know it!

23:35.860 --> 23:36.720
You know what?

23:37.650 --> 23:38.410
Let her.

23:38.940 --> 23:40.670
Mr. Spence.

23:41.490 --> 23:43.110
I just had a heart attack.

23:44.210 --> 23:46.540
"Life is short" is more
than a theory to me.

23:47.280 --> 23:49.410
I gotta be with someone
who can make me happy.

23:49.880 --> 23:52.110
Mrs. Peri wants to make you happy.

23:52.220 --> 23:53.540
Well, she had her chance.

23:54.630 --> 23:56.280
You gotta give her another one.

23:57.260 --> 23:57.870
Why?

23:59.300 --> 24:01.250
When Mrs. Evelyn caught us,

24:02.210 --> 24:04.300
I saw our reflection in the glass.

24:04.590 --> 24:07.050
And we looked like bad people.

24:07.580 --> 24:09.330
If you try to make
your marriage work

24:09.365 --> 24:10.840
and it doesn't,

24:11.400 --> 24:14.070
then maybe we can
talk about the future.

24:15.610 --> 24:18.160
But I need to know you tried, okay?

24:20.640 --> 24:21.560
Okay.

24:26.830 --> 24:27.605
So what are we gonna do

24:27.640 --> 24:29.560
about the crazy lady
that wants my kid?

24:31.610 --> 24:33.720
Maybe we should talk to the guy

24:33.755 --> 24:35.830
that was crazy enough to marry her.

24:47.270 --> 24:50.910
I did not know Alfred
spoke to Valentina.

24:51.040 --> 24:52.450
You must believe me.

24:53.310 --> 24:54.140
I do.

24:56.840 --> 25:00.380
So, is Valentina going
to go through with it?

25:00.710 --> 25:01.990
She wants to.

25:04.520 --> 25:06.340
But you're gonna
talk her out of it.

25:07.570 --> 25:09.790
You can't ask me to do that.

25:09.825 --> 25:11.565
Alfred will leave me.

25:11.600 --> 25:12.835
Let's put aside for the moment

25:12.870 --> 25:15.350
that this egg will
become my grandchild.

25:15.630 --> 25:19.470
He or she will be raised
by a man in his 70s and you.

25:19.710 --> 25:21.890
Alfred will be a wonderful father.

25:21.950 --> 25:23.605
I'm sure he'll be devoted...

25:23.640 --> 25:25.530
during the few years he has left.

25:26.380 --> 25:28.035
That's what's
bothering you-- his age?

25:28.070 --> 25:31.270
What's bothering me is
the idea that he'll die

25:31.305 --> 25:33.900
and the baby will be left with you.

25:35.640 --> 25:37.280
That's a silly thing to say.

25:37.400 --> 25:39.030
You know I'm a good mother.

25:41.470 --> 25:42.370
Zoila.

25:42.490 --> 25:44.490
I'm not saying you don't love Remi.

25:44.525 --> 25:46.490
I know you do. You just never...

25:47.400 --> 25:48.860
put him first.

25:49.310 --> 25:52.000
- That's not true.
- I was there!

25:52.035 --> 25:53.395
I saw you fall apart

25:53.430 --> 25:55.880
each time husband
number whatever left you.

25:55.915 --> 25:58.330
And you'd make Remi
pick up the pieces.

25:58.390 --> 26:00.990
God, how many times did
you interrupt his childhood

26:01.025 --> 26:02.590
pulling crap like that?

26:03.260 --> 26:06.250
So what if I was a
little unstable back then?

26:06.920 --> 26:09.890
Remi has turned out beautifully.

26:09.925 --> 26:11.592
That's what matters.

26:11.627 --> 26:13.260
He has problems.

26:14.280 --> 26:17.430
And you won't pay attention
long enough to see them.

26:19.750 --> 26:21.300
What kind of problems?

26:25.150 --> 26:26.020
Sweetie...

26:27.610 --> 26:30.310
Remi is not on a ski trip.

26:31.260 --> 26:32.100
Where is he?

26:34.060 --> 26:35.500
He's in rehab.

26:36.660 --> 26:37.900
He's using again.

26:40.120 --> 26:41.810
Why didn't anyone tell me?

26:42.040 --> 26:44.060
We were worried you'd fall apart.

26:45.290 --> 26:48.370
You didn't even give me
a chance. That's not fair.

26:48.960 --> 26:51.000
After all I've said...

26:51.950 --> 26:54.120
are you really gonna
make this about you?

26:56.720 --> 26:58.050
Is he gonna be okay?

26:58.900 --> 27:00.570
We don't know.

27:02.050 --> 27:03.290
That is why

27:03.870 --> 27:08.720
you need to tell my daughter
that you don't want her child.

27:09.980 --> 27:12.100
You need to look after your own.

27:24.290 --> 27:26.870
Hello. I'm here to
see Birdie Gladwell.

27:31.830 --> 27:33.385
Hello, Birdie.

27:33.420 --> 27:36.370
Well, look who the cat dragged in.

27:36.930 --> 27:38.190
Hey, Mirta!

27:40.400 --> 27:42.170
Don't take it personally.

27:42.390 --> 27:45.090
She's just having
one of her bad days.

27:45.125 --> 27:46.900
What's that?

27:47.630 --> 27:50.190
I bought you a little something.

27:50.580 --> 27:53.690
Well, aren't you
the sweetest thing?

27:56.210 --> 27:57.735
It's silk.

27:57.770 --> 27:58.840
Do you like it?

27:59.040 --> 28:02.080
Beats the piece of
crap my niece knit.

28:02.115 --> 28:03.700
You know... Birdie,

28:04.240 --> 28:07.070
I bet those nurses would
like to see your new scarf.

28:07.630 --> 28:10.130
They'll be green with envy.

28:12.260 --> 28:14.020
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

28:19.400 --> 28:20.630
Hello, Mirta.

28:21.540 --> 28:22.810
I'm Marisol.

28:25.280 --> 28:27.510
I just want to talk to you
about your granddaughter.

28:32.860 --> 28:33.620
Flora?

28:34.120 --> 28:35.645
Yes! Yes!

28:35.680 --> 28:37.070
I want to talk about flora.

28:39.250 --> 28:41.120
Why don't you come to see me?

28:42.020 --> 28:42.610
What?

28:43.850 --> 28:45.920
Are you angry with your abuelita?

28:58.030 --> 28:58.720
No.

28:59.440 --> 29:00.690
I'm not angry.

29:01.480 --> 29:04.530
I did not mean to
yell the last time.

29:04.565 --> 29:06.580
What you
said, it--it--

29:07.070 --> 29:09.150
it made me so ashamed.

29:10.370 --> 29:11.860
What did I say, abuela?

29:12.300 --> 29:13.610
How did I shame you?

29:15.320 --> 29:18.100
You were a bad girl, mijita.

29:18.560 --> 29:21.580
That boy--he--
he loves you.

29:22.060 --> 29:23.000
What boy?

29:24.170 --> 29:25.070
Eddie.

29:26.000 --> 29:27.070
Who else?

29:28.630 --> 29:29.970
I told you about Eddie?

29:30.005 --> 29:31.265
He loves you.

29:31.300 --> 29:33.930
I-I can see in his eyes.

29:34.190 --> 29:35.590
That's nice to hear.

29:35.840 --> 29:38.670
But you-- you are
so cruel to him.

29:40.430 --> 29:41.240
I am?

29:41.860 --> 29:43.390
The way you talk to him.

29:43.830 --> 29:46.050
Y-you take him for granted.

29:49.380 --> 29:50.980
Do you think I love Eddie...

29:51.790 --> 29:52.490
at all?

29:54.950 --> 29:56.410
In your own way.

29:57.540 --> 29:58.875
But he's not gonna marry you

29:58.910 --> 30:00.950
when he finds out you're pregnant.

30:02.220 --> 30:03.295
I told you about that?

30:03.330 --> 30:06.860
Oh, to cheat on such a nice boy.

30:07.470 --> 30:09.450
And with his friend?

30:10.680 --> 30:11.890
His friend?

30:13.230 --> 30:15.050
Did you just say "his friend"?

30:19.230 --> 30:20.360
Abuela?

30:21.310 --> 30:22.900
Oh, no, no, no, no.

30:22.910 --> 30:25.000
No, don't leave me. Stay with me.

30:25.370 --> 30:26.950
This is important.

30:50.990 --> 30:53.370
Thank you, Carmen.

31:01.310 --> 31:02.790
I'm sorry. Is there something else?

31:03.100 --> 31:03.825
I thought you should know

31:03.860 --> 31:05.700
Odessa's having her chemo tonight.

31:07.820 --> 31:08.870
Good for her.

31:11.080 --> 31:13.470
Well, if you wanted to visit her,

31:13.910 --> 31:15.510
I-I know she would appreciate it.

31:16.820 --> 31:18.300
Well, I'd love to, but I'm...

31:19.040 --> 31:20.510
swamped with work tonight.

31:23.590 --> 31:25.320
Well, she goes in two days a week.

31:25.490 --> 31:27.385
So if you can't visit her tonight,

31:27.420 --> 31:29.280
maybe you can stop by next Tuesday?

31:31.330 --> 31:32.430
I got
a--

31:32.550 --> 31:33.920
I got a thing next Tuesday.

31:33.955 --> 31:35.080
I'll tell you what.

31:35.870 --> 31:38.000
Buy Odessa some flowers...

31:40.310 --> 31:41.630
That should cheer her up.

31:49.170 --> 31:51.310
I'm annoyed. Can you tell?

31:51.410 --> 31:52.855
Have you lost your mind?!

31:52.890 --> 31:56.625
Odessa has worked
here for ten years.

31:56.660 --> 31:59.220
She has cooked and cleaned
and made up your bed

31:59.230 --> 32:01.270
and sewn buttons on your shirts.

32:01.320 --> 32:04.340
This is not just a job
for her. She adores you!

32:04.490 --> 32:06.320
I don't understand
why you can't give her

32:06.355 --> 32:08.115
- two lousy hours of your life!
- Calm down.

32:08.150 --> 32:12.230
Don't ever tell a Puerto
Rican woman to calm down.

32:12.265 --> 32:13.455
It's a waste of time!

32:13.490 --> 32:15.050
You keep talking to me like this,

32:15.060 --> 32:16.550
I'll have to fire you.

32:17.390 --> 32:18.805
I just gave you my notice.

32:18.840 --> 32:20.220
It's right there on the floor.

32:20.940 --> 32:22.060
You're quitting?

32:22.850 --> 32:24.590
Yes, I am.

32:26.000 --> 32:29.690
I only took this job because
I admired you so much.

32:29.970 --> 32:32.090
But after seeing the
way you treat people,

32:32.530 --> 32:34.750
you're no longer who I
wanna be when I grow up.

32:57.370 --> 32:58.500
You look good.

32:58.990 --> 33:00.450
Have you been able to relax?

33:00.485 --> 33:02.340
Not really.

33:02.410 --> 33:03.730
Since you were away,
I've had to meet with

33:03.765 --> 33:05.790
our broker, my
trainer, your lawyer,

33:05.825 --> 33:07.015
that caterer we both adore,

33:07.050 --> 33:09.420
and that personal
shopper we both despise.

33:09.455 --> 33:11.440
All that, and you still had time

33:11.475 --> 33:13.310
to blackmail the neighbors.

33:14.610 --> 33:16.760
You must be referring
to Spence Westmore.

33:17.490 --> 33:18.815
What could you have been thinking?

33:18.850 --> 33:21.330
Well, you know how I feel
about men who seduce the help.

33:21.365 --> 33:22.580
Just trying to teach him a lesson.

33:22.615 --> 33:24.380
I'm talking about the child.

33:28.070 --> 33:29.230
That was nothing.

33:29.300 --> 33:31.460
You demanded Rosie
bring him to our house.

33:33.990 --> 33:36.780
You haven't met
Tucker. He's special.

33:37.620 --> 33:39.490
I won't let this happen again.

33:39.880 --> 33:42.045
This isn't like last time. I swear.

33:42.080 --> 33:44.210
I've already made an
appointment with Dr. Weiller.

33:44.220 --> 33:46.230
I lost a son, and I
continue to grieve.

33:46.265 --> 33:47.725
That doesn't make me crazy.

33:47.760 --> 33:49.420
When you mistake
another woman's child

33:49.455 --> 33:51.242
for the one you buried...

33:51.277 --> 33:53.058
I wasn't confused this time.

33:53.093 --> 33:54.840
I always knew he wasn't mine.

33:54.850 --> 33:56.940
Well, I think you're still sick.

33:57.550 --> 33:58.945
And I'm gonna get you help.

33:58.980 --> 34:00.340
Is it sick to want affection?

34:02.300 --> 34:04.510
That's what children give--
even other people's children.

34:04.545 --> 34:06.720
They look into your eyes,
and they instantly love you.

34:06.755 --> 34:08.550
It's the most amazing thing.

34:08.585 --> 34:09.650
Adrian...

34:09.679 --> 34:11.050
I miss seeing love
in someone's eyes.

34:11.085 --> 34:12.420
I wondered how long
it would take you

34:12.455 --> 34:13.534
to lay this at my doorstep.

34:13.570 --> 34:16.210
Well, why shouldn't I?
I may be off the beam,

34:16.245 --> 34:17.264
but you're the one who pushed me.

34:17.300 --> 34:20.280
What, you think I choose
to be cold and unforgiving?

34:20.800 --> 34:22.280
Barrett was hit by a car.

34:22.830 --> 34:24.139
It was an accident.

34:24.690 --> 34:26.540
Isn't it time that you forgave me?

34:27.600 --> 34:28.730
I have tried.

34:30.500 --> 34:31.690
Try again.

34:34.350 --> 34:35.425
And I will forgive you

34:35.460 --> 34:37.530
every act of debauchery
you have ever committed.

34:37.540 --> 34:39.429
You can commit new
ones for all I care.

34:39.560 --> 34:40.659
Just...

34:43.310 --> 34:45.350
Look at me the way you used to.

34:46.330 --> 34:47.449
Please.

34:55.170 --> 34:56.790
Oh, god.

35:39.250 --> 35:41.420
So your son is in rehab?

35:42.030 --> 35:43.515
At a clinic in the desert.

35:43.550 --> 35:45.700
I'm gonna go visit
him for a few days.

35:45.890 --> 35:49.070
I'm sure he'll appreciate
the show of support.

35:49.105 --> 35:50.650
I certainly hope so.

35:54.010 --> 35:55.180
By the way...

35:57.520 --> 36:00.700
I had a long talk with
Valentina this morning.

36:03.530 --> 36:07.700
She's no longer interested
in giving us one of her eggs.

36:09.090 --> 36:11.510
She seemed interested yesterday.

36:12.810 --> 36:15.530
Like I said, it was a long talk.

36:16.090 --> 36:17.750
We discussed this.

36:18.300 --> 36:20.405
If you can't give me a child...

36:20.440 --> 36:23.250
You have to go
elsewhere, I understand.

36:24.140 --> 36:28.080
You don't sound particularly
sad to see me go.

36:28.990 --> 36:31.380
Oh, but I am.

36:33.940 --> 36:36.660
You are a very sweet man, Alfred.

36:37.180 --> 36:39.460
And I will miss you very much.

36:43.480 --> 36:44.840
My car is here.

36:44.990 --> 36:46.385
I'm gonna have to go.

36:46.420 --> 36:49.140
Are you absolutely sure about this?

36:50.360 --> 36:52.880
I was gonna spoil you rotten.

36:54.230 --> 36:55.800
Oh, Alfred...

36:57.750 --> 37:00.210
It's not about me anymore.

37:01.970 --> 37:03.410
Isn't it amazing?

37:25.810 --> 37:27.230
So what are you thinking?

37:28.950 --> 37:30.110
Nothing.

37:33.190 --> 37:35.165
Hey. How about...

37:35.200 --> 37:37.610
I go get us some ice cream
at the cafeteria? Hmm?

37:39.120 --> 37:40.390
If you like.

37:40.810 --> 37:41.730
Here.

37:52.120 --> 37:53.180
You came.

37:54.820 --> 37:55.820
Yeah.

37:58.210 --> 38:00.140
Odessa's gonna be so happy.

38:00.870 --> 38:01.970
Yeah, I, uh...

38:02.890 --> 38:05.390
I didn't know what I would
talk about for two hours.

38:06.260 --> 38:07.820
So... I thought maybe
I could sing to her.

38:08.980 --> 38:10.850
I think she'll be thrilled.

38:14.250 --> 38:16.370
You know the worst
part about being a star?

38:17.690 --> 38:19.000
Is people stop kicking your ass,

38:19.035 --> 38:20.310
and they start kissing it...

38:20.660 --> 38:21.800
constantly.

38:22.990 --> 38:24.360
I don't want that.

38:24.790 --> 38:27.310
Well, I'm happy to kick your ass

38:27.345 --> 38:28.760
anytime you need it.

38:29.980 --> 38:31.460
Sounds like you're not quitting.

38:31.470 --> 38:32.880
Don't listen to a
Puerto Rican woman

38:32.915 --> 38:34.670
when she's hysterical.

38:34.960 --> 38:36.510
We always exaggerate.

38:36.950 --> 38:38.040
Come on.

38:39.070 --> 38:40.190
Odessa...

38:42.230 --> 38:43.880
Someone is here to see you.

38:45.230 --> 38:46.570
Alejandro!

38:47.040 --> 38:49.640
Well, hello there.
How are you doing?

38:49.950 --> 38:51.465
You didn't need to come.

38:51.500 --> 38:52.980
Ah, of course I did.

38:53.900 --> 38:55.510
Are you ready to be entertained?

38:56.180 --> 38:58.030
You're going to sing to me?

38:59.240 --> 39:00.850
I won't even charge you for it.

39:02.340 --> 39:04.130
This is very exciting.

39:05.040 --> 39:07.230
Here's a little something
from my latest album.

39:07.560 --> 39:08.810
I hope you like it.

39:10.420 --> 39:12.620
♪Tus miradas♪

39:13.380 --> 39:16.480
♪Las palabras que florecen♪

39:16.515 --> 39:19.350
♪en tus labio♪

39:30.530 --> 39:32.270
I talked to Mrs. Delatour.

39:34.930 --> 39:37.200
She broke up with Mr. Pettigrove.

39:37.235 --> 39:39.470
So... they won't be needing my egg.

39:40.010 --> 39:41.300
Thank God.

39:43.380 --> 39:45.410
I'm sorry for the
way I spoke to you.

39:45.820 --> 39:47.940
I was just excited
about going to school

39:48.340 --> 39:49.440
and helping you.

39:51.480 --> 39:52.810
I've been thinking.

39:54.400 --> 39:57.470
Many years ago, Mrs.
Delatour gave me a ring.

39:58.100 --> 39:59.890
It's sort of expensive.

40:03.620 --> 40:05.590
I've been saving it for...

40:08.280 --> 40:10.700
I don't know. Maybe I've
been saving it for this.

40:12.410 --> 40:15.120
Anyway, I'm gonna sell it
to pay for your tuition.

40:16.520 --> 40:18.110
Mami!

40:22.760 --> 40:24.870
All right. Enough of that.

40:25.980 --> 40:28.500
- There's a bulb out in the guest room.
- I'll go change it.

40:30.960 --> 40:32.160
One more thing.

40:34.630 --> 40:36.390
Whatever sacrifices I made for you,

40:36.425 --> 40:38.350
are none of your business.

40:38.790 --> 40:41.200
All you gotta do is
grow up and be happy.

40:41.710 --> 40:44.220
Then I'll have everything
I've ever wanted, okay?

41:09.000 --> 41:10.060
- Oh!
- Sorry...

41:10.480 --> 41:11.740
I rang the bell.

41:12.360 --> 41:14.590
I know. It's broken.

41:14.600 --> 41:16.990
You got a moment? I have good news.

41:17.025 --> 41:18.140
Yes.

41:18.400 --> 41:21.130
But Mrs. Peri's plane
landed 20 minutes ago.

41:21.165 --> 41:23.220
We're expecting her any second.

41:23.240 --> 41:24.415
I spoke to my wife.

41:24.450 --> 41:26.530
She will not say a word to anyone

41:26.565 --> 41:28.270
about what she saw here.

41:28.390 --> 41:29.890
Thank God.

41:30.090 --> 41:31.380
And the baby?

41:32.370 --> 41:35.840
Her interest in Tucker
has been... resolved.

41:35.870 --> 41:38.170
Oh, this is such a relief.

41:38.890 --> 41:41.090
Thank you for your
help, Mr. Adrian.

41:41.125 --> 41:42.770
I really owe you one.

41:48.120 --> 41:50.550
You absolutely do.

